{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "dra:sirach.30",
    "translationId": "dra",
    "bookSlug": "sirach",
    "chapterNumber": 30,
    "referenceLabel": "Sirach 30",
    "summary": "Source text for Sirach 30 in Douay-Rheims Bible (Challoner)."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.30.1",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 30:1",
      "text": "He that loveth his son, frequently chastiseth him, that he may rejoice in his latter end, and not grope after the doors of his neighbours.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.30.2",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 30:2",
      "text": "He that instructeth his son shall be praised in him, and shall glory in him in the midst of them of his household.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.30.3",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 30:3",
      "text": "He that teacheth his son, maketh his enemy jealous, and in the midst of his friends he shall glory in him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.30.4",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 30:4",
      "text": "His father is dead, and he is as if he were not dead: for he hath left one behind him that is like himself.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.30.5",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 30:5",
      "text": "While he lived he saw and rejoiced in him: and when he died he was not sorrowful, neither was he confounded before his enemies.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.30.6",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 30:6",
      "text": "For he left behind him a defender of his house against his enemies, and one that will requite kindness to his friends.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.30.7",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 30:7",
      "text": "For the souls of his sons he shall bind up his wounds, and at every cry his bowels shall be troubled.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.30.8",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 30:8",
      "text": "A horse not broken becometh stubborn, and a child left to himself will become headstrong.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.30.9",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 30:9",
      "text": "Give thy son his way, and he shall make thee afraid: play with him, and he shall make thee sorrowful.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.30.10",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 30:10",
      "text": "Laugh not with him, lest thou have sorrow, and at the last thy teeth be set on edge.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.30.11",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 30:11",
      "text": "Give him not liberty in his youth, and wink not at his devices.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.30.12",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 30:12",
      "text": "Bow down his neck while he is young, and beat his sides while he is a child, lest he grow stubborn, and regard thee not, and so be a sorrow of heart to thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.30.13",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 30:13",
      "text": "Instruct thy son, and labour about him, lest his lewd behaviour be an offence to thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.30.14",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 30:14",
      "text": "Better is a poor man who is sound, and strong of constitution, than a rich man who is weak and afflicted with evils.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.30.15",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 30:15",
      "text": "Health of the soul in holiness of justice, is better than all gold and silver: and a sound body, than immense revenues.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.30.16",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 30:16",
      "text": "There is no riches above the riches of the health of the body: and there is no pleasure above the joy of the heart.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.30.17",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 30:17",
      "text": "Better is death than a bitter life, and everlasting rest, than continual sickness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.30.18",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 30:18",
      "text": "Good things that are hidden in a mouth that is shut, are as messes of meat set about a grave.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.30.19",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 30:19",
      "text": "What good shall an offering do to an idol? for it can neither eat, nor smell:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.30.20",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 30:20",
      "text": "So is he that is persecuted by the Lord, bearing the reward of his iniquity:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.30.21",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 30:21",
      "text": "He seeth with his eyes, and groaneth, as an eunuch embracing a virgin, and sighing.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.30.22",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 30:22",
      "text": "Give not up thy soul to sadness, and afflict not thyself in thy own counsel.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.30.23",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 30:23",
      "text": "The joyfulness of the heart, is the life of a man, and a never failing treasure of holiness: and the joy of a man is length of life.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.30.24",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 30:24",
      "text": "Have pity on thy own soul, pleasing God, and contain thyself: gather up thy heart in his holiness: and drive away sadness far from thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.30.25",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 30:25",
      "text": "For sadness hath killed many, and there is no profit in it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.30.26",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 30:26",
      "text": "Envy and anger shorten a man's days, and pensiveness will bring old age before the time.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.30.27",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 30:27",
      "text": "A cheerful and good heart is always feasting: for his banquets are prepared with diligence.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
